    "b434: scrubbed the faint green edge-fringe off the now-transparent sprites. After the Gemini key, anti-aliased silhouettes still carried a sliver of the key green -- near-invisible on the dark game panels but visible on lighter backdrops. New sprite_package/code/despill_pool.py does a post-hoc edge-band despill straight on the canonical pool: for every RGBA sprite it pulls the green channel down to max(R,B) in the ring of opaque pixels within 2px of transparency, leaving interiors untouched so genuinely green creatures (serpents, dragons, green-skinned mages) keep their colour. Ran over all 1,321 in-game sprites; edges are clean on any background now.",
